				<position book_orientation="270" place="right_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						In propria cuiusq[ue] singularis professoris facultate; da mihi
						vnicam praxin mundi, qua[e] prorsus radicalis est; et
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="270" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						singulis Solis annis;
						Luna[e] mensibus; 
						omniu[m] planetaru[m]
						diebus, atq[ue] horis
						sibi constat, =
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="270" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						= quantum vllo modo crescere potest, semper magis, magisq[ue] extensa.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Against the special ability of any singular professor, give me the unique praxis of the world, 
				which is entirely radical and which remains consistent with itself throughout each single year of the Sun,
				the months of the Moon, and the days and hours of all the planets.
				It is able to grow in any way possible, becoming more and more extensive.
			</translation>
